==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: clostridium
<hw>clostridium</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <plu><plw>clostridia</plw></plu>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>spindle-shaped bacterial cell esp. one swollen at the
center by an endospore.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> clostridia.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[capitalized]</mark> <def>a genus of anaerobic,
spore-forming motile bacteria of the family <fam>Bacillaceae</fam>,
including several pathogenic species, such as the causative agents of
<causes>gas gangrene</causes> (<styp><spn>Clostridium
perfringens</spn></styp>), <causes>botulism</causes>
(<stype><spn>Clostridium botulinum</spn></stype>), and
<causes>tetanus</causes> (<styp><spn>Clostridium
tetani</spn></styp>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Closure</ent>⟦br⟧
